<html>
<head>
<style>
        /*   unvisited link   */
a:link
{
    color:blue;
}
     /*  visited link  */
a:visited
{
      color:green;
}
       /*  mouse over link  */
a:active
{
        color:red;

}
       /*  selected link   */
a:active
{
      color:yellow;
}
</style>
</head>
<body bgcolor="pale red">
<h2>CSS link</h2>
<p><b><a href="defaut.html"target="-blank">This is a link</a></b></p>
<p><b>NOTE:</b><font color="black">   In CSS, the term "box model" is used when talking about design and layout. The CSS box model is essentially a box that wraps around every HTML element.</p></font>
</body>
</html>